```js
if (document.readyState === 'loading') {
  window.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', startApp, { once: true });
} else {
  startApp();
}
```

Top-level `await import('./pdfjs/web/pdf_viewer.mjs')` makes the module async; DOMContentLoaded has already fired by the time the dynamic import resolves, so a late listener never executes.

Include `theme-dark-pages` wherever the viewer should use the dark chrome background:

```css
body.theme-dark #viewerContainer,
body.theme-dark-pages #viewerContainer,
body.theme-inverted #viewerContainer {
  background: #1f1f1f;
}
```

Do NOT add a filter for theme-dark-pages -- PDF.js does the recoloring on canvas. Keep the existing `theme-inverted .pdfViewer .page` filter unchanged. Only adjust annotation popup/text-layer colors after visual QA, and only if demonstrably wrong.

